        <hl1>Fuzzy Math on Greenhouse Gas</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ben Cramer letter holds Pres Bush's climate policy is like 5-cent tip on $100 restaurant bill: more insulting than leaving nothing at all; contends it should spur rest of world into action--to quickly ratify Kyoto treaty without delay</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Bush Plan Expected to Slow, Not Halt, Gas Emission Rise'' (front page, Feb. 14):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Bush Plan Expected to Slow, Not Halt, Gas Emission Rise'' (front page, Feb. 14):</p>
        <p>President Bush's climate policy is like a 5-cent tip on a $100 restaurant bill: more insulting than leaving nothing at all. It should spur the rest of the world into action -- to quickly ratify the Kyoto treaty without delay.</p>
        <p>BEN CRAMER  Piscataway, N.J., Feb. 15, 2002</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
